Czech Equities Fall to Month-Low as Erste Bank, New World Slump

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-01T16:19:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/czech-stocks-fall-after-two-day-rally-as-cez-nwr-erste-slump.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark stock
index slumped to a one-month low as  Erste Group Bank AG  and coal
company  New World Resources NV  lost more than 1.9 percent.  The PX gauge, where NWR and Erste have a combined weighting
of about 35 percent, fell 1.1 percent to 1,230.6 at its 4:28
p.m. close in Prague, its lowest level since Jan. 28.  Austria’s Erste slid 2.9 percent, the most in more than a
month, to 911 koruna. NWR slumped 2 percent to 274.1 koruna,
snapping a four-day advance. CEZ AS, the biggest Czech power
utility, retreated 0.6 percent to 805 koruna, its lowest close
in two weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
